AB  - Freak storms around the U.K.'s coast could be the first signs of a new wave climate requiring a reevaluation of coastal defence policy. Although global warming was raising sea levels annually, it did not account for the changes in wave behaviour. New and accurate data on these wave patterns are essential as equations governing the design of defences are related to the cube of the wave height, a 10% error in approximate wave height causing a 33% error in the design. The technology and use of wave recorders is discussed. -P.M.Taylor
KW  - coastal protection;  design waves;  wave motion, coastal protection;  wave patterns
